<subSubSection id="999237A7FFFBAC01479DFA43FC2EFA48" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D137642CFFFBAC01479DFA43FC2EFA48" blockId="1.[136,1452,764,2051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC01479DFA43FEEBFAAC" bold="true" box="[189,318,1376,1402]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The epithet is given in honor of Belgian Phycologist Dr. Pierre Compère (1934–2016), author of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC0147DAFAA7FE10FA48" authorityName="Compere" authorityYear="1977" box="[250,453,1412,1438]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC0147DAFAA7FE10FA48" box="[250,453,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">Bourrellyodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for his contribution to the knowledge of desmids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="999237A7FFFBAC03479DFA8BFED8F9CA" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D137642CFFFBAC01479DFA8BFB34F9DD" blockId="1.[136,1452,764,2051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC01479DFA8BFE69FA14" bold="true" box="[189,444,1448,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC0146C0FA8BFCCCFA14" authorityName="M. A. Santos &amp; C. W. N. Moura" authorityYear="2022" box="[480,793,1448,1474]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="comperei">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC0146C0FA8BFCCCFA14" box="[480,793,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">Bourrellyodesmus comperei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species of the genus by having elliptical cells in apical view, parallel sides, acute-rounded angles with 1 short spine, 1 tiny intramarginal granule on each side, near the spine, and 1 median intumescence in each semicell, with a diagonal-opposite arrangement.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D137642CFFFBAC01479DF937FED7F8D0" blockId="1.[136,1452,764,2051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC0146A6F936FDDEF9F8" authorityName="M. A. Santos &amp; C. W. N. Moura" authorityYear="2022" box="[390,523,1557,1582]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="comperei">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC0146A6F936FDDEF9F8" box="[390,523,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">B. comperei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a cell shape similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC0144A7F936FF6BF984" authority="C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; Compere (1978: 419)" authorityName="C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; Compere" authorityPageNumber="419" authorityYear="1978" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="sumatranus">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC0144A7F936FBFCF9F8" box="[903,1065,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">B. sumatranus</emphasis>
C.E.M. 
<bibRefCitation id="B51919DDFFFBAC01435AF937FF6BF984" author="Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Compere, P." pageId="1" pageNumber="229" pagination="409 - 426" refId="ref7038" refString="Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Compere, P. (1978) A taxonomic study of the desmid genus Bourrellyodesmus (Zygnemaphyceae). Bulletim du Jardin Botanique National de Belgique 48: 409 - 426. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3667941" type="journal article" year="1978">Bicudo &amp; Compère (1978: 419)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a rare species, described in 
<collectingCountry id="A99F24BCFFFBAC0146D7F91BFDB2F984" box="[503,615,1592,1618]" name="Indonesia" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, South of Palembang, Kaju-Agung, 
<collectingRegion id="134CAACEFFFBAC0144D7F91BFB4AF984" box="[1015,1183,1592,1618]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Selatan" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">South Sumatra</collectingRegion>
. However, the semicells of 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC014788F97EFE99F9A0" authorityName="C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; Compere" authorityYear="1978" box="[168,332,1629,1654]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="sumatranus">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC014788F97EFE99F9A0" box="[168,332,1629,1654]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">B. sumatranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct in that they have a convergent facial granule near the isthmus, conical (frontal view), or emarginate (apical view), with no tiny intramarginal granules on apical angles. 
<bibRefCitation id="B51919DDFFFBAC01436FF9A3FADEF94C" author="Compere, P." box="[1103,1291,1664,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" pagination="141 - 160" refId="ref7442" refString="Compere, P. (1983) Some algae from Kashmir and Ladakh, W. Himalayas. Bulletin de la Societe Royale de Botanique de Belgique / Bulletin van de KoninklijkeBelgische Botanische Vereniging 116 (2): 141 - 160." type="journal article" year="1983">Compère (1983)</bibRefCitation>
characterized specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC014608F986FE1BF968" authorityName="C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; Compere" authorityYear="1978" box="[296,462,1701,1726]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="sumatranus">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC014608F986FE1BF968" box="[296,462,1701,1726]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">B. sumatranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected at the Himalayas as having less trapezoidal semicells and the apical angles ornate with two tiny teethes, differing in this aspect from the 
<typeStatus id="0E33DA8EFFFBAC01441DF9EAFCB8F935" box="[829,877,1737,1763]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">type</typeStatus>
material and specimens analyzed in the Marimbus do Baiano.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D137642CFFFBAC01479DF833FD0EF7D4" blockId="1.[136,1452,764,2051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC01479DF833FE2BF8FC" authorityName="M. A. Santos &amp; C. W. N. Moura" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,510,1808,1834]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="comperei">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC01479DF833FE2BF8FC" box="[189,510,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">Bourrellyodesmus comperei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also presents some morphological similarities between the lateral and apical views of 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC0147D5F816FB09F899" authority="(C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; M. T. P. Azevedo) C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; Compere (1978: 416)" authorityName="C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; Compere" authorityPageNumber="416" authorityYear="1978" baseAuthorityName="C. E. M. Bicudo &amp; M. T. P. Azevedo" box="[245,1244,1844,1871]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="jolyanus">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC0147D5F816FEA2F898" box="[245,375,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">B. jolyanus</emphasis>
(C.E.M.Bicudo &amp; M.T.P.Azevedo) C.E.M. 
<bibRefCitation id="B51919DDFFFBAC014442F817FB09F899" author="Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Compere, P." box="[866,1244,1844,1871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" pagination="409 - 426" refId="ref7038" refString="Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Compere, P. (1978) A taxonomic study of the desmid genus Bourrellyodesmus (Zygnemaphyceae). Bulletim du Jardin Botanique National de Belgique 48: 409 - 426. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3667941" type="journal article" year="1978">Bicudo &amp; Compère (1978: 416)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="16881FAFFFFBAC014238F816FD5BF8A5" authority="S. M. M. Faustino &amp; C. E. M. Bicudo (2004: 669)" authorityName="S. M. M. Faustino &amp; C. E. M. Bicudo" authorityPageNumber="669" authorityYear="2004" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Bourrellyodesmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="229" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="guarrerae">
<emphasis id="E3FCB83EFFFBAC014238F816FA79F898" box="[1304,1452,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">B. guarrerae</emphasis>
S.M.M.Faustino &amp; C.E.M.Bicudo (2004: 669)
</taxonomicName>
, both of which are described in 
<collectingRegion id="134CAACEFFFBAC0144CFF87BFBB7F8A4" box="[1007,1122,1880,1906]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A99F24BCFFFBAC01434CF87BFB61F8A4" box="[1132,1204,1880,1906]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="229">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The former differs by having an apical view with 2 intramarginal granules on each side, near the spines, and 1 median swelling, and by the largest size (23.0–27.0 μm × 21.0–24.0 μm); whereas the latter species differs in lateral view by having a short acute spine on granule located in the center of each semicell. Therefore, we consider that these morphological differences are enough to describe our material as a new species.
</paragraph>
